  Key Changes

  1. ContextFirstMixin Extended (/core/services/context_first_mixin.py):
    - Added _configure_rich_context() for domain configuration
    - Added _get_entity_dict_from_rich_context() for entity lookup
    - Added _get_graph_context_from_rich() for relationship extraction
    - Added logging helpers for context hit/miss tracking
    - Added parsing helpers: parse_date_field(), parse_datetime_field(), parse_enum_field(), extract_uids_from_graph_context()

  2. Pattern Applied: For each service method that receives UserContext:
    - Build lookup dict from rich context for O(1) access
    - Check rich context FIRST before querying Neo4j
    - Extract entity data and relationships from graph_context
    - Log context hits vs Neo4j queries for monitoring
    - Fall back to Neo4j only when data not in rich context

  3. Benefits:
    - Zero queries when data is in rich context
    - Single source of truth (UserContext)
    - Consistent pattern across all domains
    - Observable efficiency via logging

  4. Tests: All 25 context-first pattern tests pass.

